# Nonlinear TC diagonal self-loop: the exactly-once + termination witness.
# A single self-loop edge(7,7) ties both same-stratum join positions to the
# same p(7,7) row; the self-join instance must fire exactly once per round.
# Batch 1 adds edge(7,7) (p(7,7) present, recursion terminates); batch 2
# removes it (the self-supporting diagonal drains to empty).
# Truth: after add reachable={(7,7)}; after remove reachable={}.
batch
+ add_edge 7 7
end
batch
- add_edge 7 7
end
